# Entity and Chain Name Casing

When displaying or generating entity/chain names (nursing home chains, affiliated entities):

- Use **title case** for the full name (e.g. "NHS Management", not "NHS MANAGEMENT" or "nhs management").
- **Preserve known acronyms in all-caps** when they appear as words in the name. Examples:
  - "Nhs management" → **NHS Management**
  - "Genesis Healthcare" → unchanged
  - Names containing CMS, RN, LPN, CCRC, PBJ, HPRD, SNF, ALF, LTAC, ID/DD should keep those tokens in all-caps.

In this codebase, `capitalize_entity_name()` in `app.py` applies this logic. When adding new acronyms that should stay all-caps, add them to `ENTITY_NAME_ACRONYMS` and ensure display paths (provider pages, entity pages, search index, breadcrumbs) use `capitalize_entity_name()` for entity/chain names.
